# üìù ZenAI Commit Template
#
# Use Conventional Commit format: <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Examples:
#   feat(prompt_framework): add DETAIL vs BASIC mode handling
#   fix(validation): prevent marking tasks complete before checklist pass
#   docs(security): clarify memory zeroing requirements
#   chore(init): initial commit with full ZenAI folder structure
#   refactor(cursor_rules): simplify feedback loop logic
#
# Common types:
#   feat     ‚Üí new feature
#   fix      ‚Üí bug fix
#   docs     ‚Üí documentation only
#   style    ‚Üí formatting only (no logic changes)
#   refactor ‚Üí code refactoring (no new features or fixes)
#   test     ‚Üí adding or updating tests
#   chore    ‚Üí repo setup, scaffolding, task hygiene
#   ci       ‚Üí continuous integration changes
#
# Common scopes (freeform, lowercase recommended):
#   prompt_framework, projectplan, validation, milestone_0, cursor_rules,
#   readme, security, repo, checklist
#
# Use the area below to write your message. The first line will be used as the commit subject.
# Leave a blank line after the subject, then add an optional body if needed.

<type>(<scope>): <commit message here>

